sec.p:
In the first spring of 2019, a new Muscari record was reported for the flora of Turkey (
Eker et al. 2019
). When we examined the mentioned publication, it was thought that the specimens with pictures taken of nature, detailed descriptions and identified as Muscari pallens (M.Bieb.) Fischer (1812: 9) might be belong to a different species. Afterwards, detailed studies were carried out by collecting samples from the natural distribution area within the scope of the TUBITAK project named as “The Revision of the Turkish Muscari genus”. As a result of the examinations based on both the literature and herbarium samples, as well as the checking of the flora of the nearby countries, it was concluded that our foresight was correct, and the existence of a new species was reached.

